snippet.textDisplay: I got a feeling Conor is resurrecting this year and Khabib is on the down.  I had the same feeling after the Aldo fight that Conor reached peak and it would soon change, and in less than a year, it did.  With Khabib, I get the same feeling:  fighters from his gym are popping and taking some serious L's, just as. SBG peaked out in the Conor Era.  It is so hard to maintain greatness in this sport for a long time, especially when you get popular.  Khabib beat Dustin, yes, but you can see he's slipping - taking more damage and harder shots than ever before, much like GSP's wrestle blanket domination started winning, as he started getting rounds taken and rocked.  Gaethje is his Hendricks if Conor does not get him first.

snippet.textDisplay:
I think that Conor Mcgregor would lose a rematch against Khabib Nurmagomedov.
And I have my doubts about his prospects against a crazy fighter like Tony Ferguson.
Jorge Masvidal? No way I can see Mcgregor defeating him.
By now, people know Mcgregor's style : great boxing with a diversity of different strikes (front kicks, straight left punches, combinations, lightening quick counters), yet not that much quality when it comes to ground game and a tendency to gas in the 4th and 5th rounds.
Most superchampions started out koing people quickly : George St-Pierre, Jose Aldo, Anderson Silva, etc. After awhile they have to face tougher and smarter opposition. It gets harder to win against better fighters.
And then there's those younger and hungrier fighters who were sweating blood and fighting hard fights while Mcgregor was on hiatus trying to sell his shitty whisky and punching drunk old guys at some pub.

snippet.textDisplay:
I get all the trash talk as a tool some fighters use to, more than try to get into the head of the opponent, motivate themselves for big fights : if one talks too much , that fighter will have to back it up once the fight takes place, which might serve the purpose of making the fighter train as hard as he can for that particular event.

Problem is : when that kind of talkative fighter starts losing fights, then he loses credibility when talking before a fight. The fans know that he's done that before and couldn't back it up in the past.
